rComments: Tough course, marking was harsh (not profs fault, but TAs). Final is fair. Must review lecture material once a week to grasp the content.

Hes a cool guy and is very knowledgeable, but definitely needs to review his teaching methods. Luckily the final was bell curved because I really did learn a lot, and to fail a class after learning so much would be disappointing.

He can not finish the course in last few days. He just randomly jumps around the chapters. I did't give us any homework and solution during the whole course. There just two exams each worth 50%!!! Not a fair course at all. Don't choose him!!!

what he teaches is simple, then when you go to write his exam you will think your reading a different language he makes it unbelievably hard, avoid taking his courses Not helpful if you email him either

His English is good since he is a native speaker. His math is poor. He just talks and talks. He showed us a previous exam given by him. There is a problem on law of large numbers. He asked us to take log to make product a sum, but the variables are not independent as required by the textbook. Avoid him.
Most approachable professor at UTSC. Really nice guy and always willing to help. The material is difficult but he's clearly trying his best to make it entertaining
